The Herald Eight people were last night burnt to death when a Kanyemba bound kombi was side-swiped by a lorry near Mutorashanga Turn Off. Acting Mashonaland Central Development Coordinator, Mr Cosmas Chiringa confirmed the accident which happened around 7 pm. <img class="wp-image-459969 size-large" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/kombi-2-510x680.jpg" alt="" width="510" height="680" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/kombi-2-510x680.jpg 510w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/kombi-2-270x360.jpg 270w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/kombi-2-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/kombi-2.jpg 810w" sizes="(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px" /> A shell of the kombi in which eight passengers perished in Kanyemba He said the kombi which had nine passengers including the driver was coming from Concession when it side-swiped with a lorry resulting in it bursting into flames which killed the eight people. Only the conductor survived the horror accident.